|\n+54: | `DYNAMODB_CLIENTS_TABLE` | `GFF_CLIENTS` | DynamoDB Client registry table |\n+55: | `DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TABLE` | `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS` | Multi-tenant single-table records |\n+56: | `S3_DOCUMENTS_BUCKET` | `gff-portal-documents-prod` | Secure S3 bucket name |\n+57: | `JWT_SECRET` | *cryptographically_secure_256_bit_signature_key* | Token signature key |\n+58: \n+59: #### Frontend Variables (`.env.production`)\n+60: | Variable Name | Required Value/Format | Purpose |\n+61: | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n+62: | `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` | `https://api.gff.ai/v1` | URL of the production FastAPI gateway |\n+63: | `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV` | `production` | Deployment stage tag |\n+64: | `NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_UPLOADS_ENABLED` | `true` | Enable upload features on the portal |\n+65: | `NEXT_PUBLIC_S3_BUCKET_NAME` | `gff-portal-documents-prod` | Target S3 bucket name |\n+66: \n+67: ---\n+68: \n+69: ### 2. Operational Start & Build Commands\n+70: \n+71: #### FastAPI Backend (ASGI Server)\n+72: ```bash\n+73: # Production start command\n+74: uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --workers 4\n+75: ```\n+76: \n+77: #### Next.js Frontend (Build & Run)\n+78: ```bash\n+79: # Production build command\n+80: npm run build\n+81: \n+82: # Production start command\n+83: npm run start\n+84: ```\n+85: \n+86: ---\n+87: \n+88: ### 3. AWS Resource Names\n+89: Ensure these exact resources are provisioned in AWS:\n+90: - **DynamoDB Table (Users)**: `GFF_USERS`\n+91: - **DynamoDB Table (Clients)**: `GFF_CLIENTS`\n+92: - **DynamoDB Table (Single-Table Core Items)**: `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS` (Index: `GSI1`)\n+93: - **S3 Bucket (Client Documents)**: `gff-portal-documents-prod`\n+94: \n+95: For complete architectural details, schema designs, IAM policy templates, and step-by-step production runbooks, read the [Phase 6 AWS Production Deployment & Data Modeling Guide](./docs/PHASE_6_AWS_FINAL_SETUP.md).\n+96: \n+97: \n```","success":true},"durationMs":2}}
