{"ts":"2026-06-27T22:45:40.813Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"kkggq31n","input":{"summary":"1. **Files Changed**:\n   - `docs/PHASE_6_AWS_FINAL_SETUP.md`\n   - `backend/README.md`\n   - `README.md` (root directory)\n\n2. **Summary of Implementation**:\n   - **CORS & Environment Handling**: Verified that the FastAPI backend correctly reads the `CORS_ORIGINS` environment variable dynamically and robustly parses multi-origin lists or single-origin domains to allow the appropriate frontend domains.\n   - **Deployment Manual**: Created a comprehensive execution manual describing local dev setups, backend ASGI start commands (`uvicorn app.main:app`), and frontend Next.js production build/start commands (`npm run build` & `npm run start`).\n   - **Environment Parameter Index**: Documented all required environment variables for the Next.js frontend (e.g. `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL`) and the FastAPI backend (e.g. `CORS_ORIGINS`, `JWT_SECRET`).\n   - **AWS Cloud Resources Inventory**: Clearly outlined the exact DynamoDB table names (`GFF_USERS`, `GFF_CLIENTS`, `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS` single-table schema with GSI1 support) and S3 bucket structures (`gff-portal-documents-prod`) required for production cloud migration.\n   - **Guardrails Preservation**: Preserved approved landing page configurations and avoided the insertion of any fake metrics, logos, dashboards, or unnecessary cloud configuration files.\n\n3. **Validation Done**:\n   - Ran complete backend validation checks (`npm run backend:check`) including RBAC role verification, multi-tenant isolation, and database connection checks. All tests completed successfully.","verified":true}}}
